Azure WebJobs allow developers to run background tasks within an App Service environment.

They can be:

* Continuous
* Scheduled
* Triggered

For example, a WebJob can process uploaded images or send email notifications.

A real-life use case is batch processing tasks such as generating reports or cleaning up data.

Another example is handling asynchronous tasks that should not block user requests.

WebJobs enhance application functionality by offloading background work.
